    "name": "Claude Conversation with API Metadata",
    "description": "Shows how ContextFlow captures full API details when using your own token",
    "tags": [
      "claude",
      "api-metadata",
      "cost-tracking"
    ]
  },
  "conversations": [
    {
      "id": "conv-003",
      "title": "Debug Python async issue",
      "created": "2025-10-06T15:00:00Z",
      "source": "claude",
      "messages": [
        {
          "role": "user",
          "content": "My async function is blocking. Here's the code:\n\n```python\nasync def fetch_data():\n    result = requests.get(url)  # This blocks!\n    return result.json()\n```",
          "timestamp": "2025-10-06T15:00:00Z"
        },
        {
          "role": "assistant",
          "content": "The issue is that `requests.get()` is a synchronous blocking call. In an async function, you need to use an async HTTP client like `httpx` or `aiohttp`:\n\n```python\nimport httpx\n\nasync def fetch_data():\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n        response = await client.get(url)\n        return response.json()\n```\n\nThis allows the event loop to handle other tasks while waiting for the HTTP response.",
          "timestamp": "2025-10-06T15:00:18Z",
          "api_call": {
            "provider": "anthropic",
            "model": "claude-3-5-sonnet-20241022",
            "request_id": "msg_01XFDUDYJgAACzvnptvVoYEL",
            "parameters": {
              "temperature": 0.7,
              "max_tokens": 4000,
              "top_p": 1.0
            },
            "usage": {
              "input_tokens": 45,
              "output_tokens": 89,
              "total_tokens": 134
            },
            "cost": {
              "input_cost": 0.000135,
              "output_cost": 0.00133,
              "total_cost": 0.001465,
              "currency": "USD"
            },
            "latency_ms": 1205,
            "finish_reason": "end_turn"
          }
        },
        {
          "role": "user",
          "content": "Perfect! What if I need to make multiple requests in parallel?",
          "timestamp": "2025-10-06T15:01:00Z"
        },
        {
          "role": "assistant",
          "content": "You can use `asyncio.gather()` to run multiple async requests concurrently:\n\n```python\nimport asyncio\nimport httpx\n\nasync def fetch_all(urls: list[str]):\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n        tasks = [client.get(url) for url in urls]\n        responses = await asyncio.gather(*tasks)\n        return [r.json() for r in responses]\n```\n\nThis fetches all URLs in parallel, significantly faster than sequential requests.",
          "timestamp": "2025-10-06T15:01:15Z",
          "api_call": {
            "provider": "anthropic",
            "model": "claude-3-5-sonnet-20241022",
            "request_id": "msg_02ABCDEFGhIJKlMNoPQrStUv",
            "parameters": {
              "temperature": 0.7,
              "max_tokens": 4000,
              "top_p": 1.0
            },
            "usage": {
              "input_tokens": 152,
              "output_tokens": 72,
              "total_tokens": 224
            },
            "cost": {
              "input_cost": 0.000456,
              "output_cost": 0.00108,
              "total_cost": 0.001536,
              "currency": "USD"
            },
            "latency_ms": 985,
            "finish_reason": "end_turn"
          }
        }
      ],
